arts.ttl: Lionel Messi scores 2 goals and Inter Miami clinches playoff spot with 4-0 win over New York City FC
arts.sum: After his first-half assist, Messi became the first player in MLS history to record at least 35 goal contributions in consecutive seasons. Lionel Messi had two goals and an assist to reach 37 goal contributions this season and Inter Miami clinched a playoff spot with a 4-0 victory over New York City FC on Wednesday night.
